==Indonesian==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ms|id}} {{term|kami|lang=ms}}, from {{proto|poz-mly-pro|kami|lang=id}}, from {{proto|poz-pro|kami|lang=id}}, from {{proto|map-pro|kami|lang=id}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/kami/|lang=id}}

===Pronoun===
{{head|id|pronoun}}

# [[we]] (exclusive); I and other(s) but not those ones I am addressing to.
#: ''"Kami sudah pergi ke pasar''": "We have been to the market"
# [[us]]  (exclusive); me and other(s) but not  those ones I am addressing to.
#: ''Ibu: "Kamu sekalian sudah di mandi?"'' Mother: "Have you all bathed yet?"
#: Anak-anak: "Kami?" Children: "Us?"
# [[our]]  (exclusive); my and of other(s) but not of those ones I am addressing to.
#: ''"Adalah cicak besar di dinding kamar hotel kami: tolong bantu di ambil "'': "There is a big gecko in our hotel room: please help have it removed."
# [[ours]] (if used with [[milik]], [[punya|kepunyaan]], etc.)
#: ''"Hak Milik tanah bangsa Indonesia hanya untuk kami sekalian"'': "It is only we [Indonesians] who have the right to own this Indonesian land"

